name: Jsdoc-githubify-inject
tagline: Injects jsdoc styles into pages that have been jsdoc-githubified.
body:
Simply drag the bookmarklet below to your bookmarks bar.



Now when you are on a page that has githubified jsdocs added to either a github Wiki or a github Readme, you can simply click on the bookmarklet to add styles that make it pretty.

In case you this page by accident please review [wicked](https://github.com/thlorenz/wicked) to learn how to add jsdoc API pages to your wiki.
note: Don't delete this file! It's used internally to help with page regeneration.
